file: means the file origin of this line
folder: means the folder of origin from the query
db: means the database of the result
sallseqid: means All subject Seq-id(s), separated by a ';'
qstart: means Start of alignment in query
qend: means End of alignment in query
sstart: means Start of alignment in subject
send: means End of alignment in subject
frames: means Query and subject frames separated by a '/'
staxids: means unique Subject Taxonomy ID(s), separated by a ';'(in numerical order)
sscinames: means unique Subject Scientific Name(s), separated by a ';'
scomnames: means unique Subject Common Name(s), separated by a ';'
sblastnames: means unique Subject Blast Name(s), separated by a ';' (in alphabetical order)
sskingdoms: means unique Subject Super Kingdom(s), separated by a ';' (in alphabetical order)
salltitles: means All Subject Title(s), separated by a '<>'
qseq: means Aligned part of query sequence
sseq: means Aligned part of subject sequence
contig_count: means number of results for this contig with less identity
nt_orf_frame+1: means longest nucleotide on read frame1 alignment
nt_orf_frame+1_len: means length of longest nucleotide on read frame1 alignment
aa_orf_frame+1: means longest amino-acid on read frame1 alignment
aa_orf_frame+1_len: means length of longest amino-acid on read frame1 alignment
nt_orf_frame+2: means longest nucleotide on read frame2 alignment
nt_orf_frame+2_len: means length of longest nucleotide on read frame2 alignment
aa_orf_frame+2: means longest amino-acid on read frame2 alignment
aa_orf_frame+2_len: means length of longest amino-acid on read frame2 alignment
nt_orf_frame+3: means longest nucleotide on read frame3 alignment
nt_orf_frame+3_len: means length of longest nucleotide on read frame3 alignment
aa_orf_frame+3: means longest amino-acid on read frame3 alignment
aa_orf_frame+3_len: means length of longest amino-acid on read frame3 alignment
nt_orf_frame-1: means longest nucleotide on read frame-1 alignment
nt_orf_frame-1_len: means length of longest nucleotide on read frame-1 alignment
aa_orf_frame-1: means longest amino-acid on read frame-1 alignment
aa_orf_frame-1_len: means length of longest amino-acid on read frame-1 alignment
nt_orf_frame-2: means longest nucleotide on read frame-2 alignment
nt_orf_frame-2_len: means length of longest nucleotide on read frame-2 alignment
aa_orf_frame-2: means longest amino-acid on read frame-2 alignment
aa_orf_frame-2_len: means length of longest amino-acid on read frame-2 alignment
nt_orf_frame-3: means longest nucleotide on read frame-3 alignment
nt_orf_frame-3_len: means length of longest nucleotide on read frame-3 alignment
aa_orf_frame-3: means longest amino-acid on read frame-3 alignment
aa_orf_frame-3_len: means length of longest amino-acid on read frame-3 alignment
nt_longest_orf: means longest nucleotide orf in alignment
nt_longest_orf_len: means length of longest nucleotide orf in alignment
aa_longest_orf: means longest amino-acid orf in alignment
aa_longest_orf_len: means length of longest amino-acid orf in alignment
